JOHANNESBURG (miningweekly.com) &ndash; Coal of Africa Limited (CoAL) on Wednesday said ArcelorMittal South Africa (AMSA) was no longer classified as a substantial shareholder in the miner. AMSA&rsquo;s shareholding in CoAL has decreased to 126-million ordinary shares, or 4.93% of CoAL&rsquo;s shares. The decrease in shareholding was due to the recent shareholder approved share placement of 340-million additional shares issued to Yishun Brightrise Investment, M &amp; G Investment Management and Summer Trees on June 15.